Heres what inside Embedding layer
You throw an input sequence and it will give you a list of embedded vector of each element by just checking in throught the lookup table which contains all the
embedded vectors against the whole vocab. Please note that we are using batch_size as 1 (one row at a me) which means every row can have dierent
input_sequence
Now heres what inside our RNN layer
The output of the embedding layer containing list of vectors are passed 1 by 1 aer each me step
And nally heres what the linear layer looks like
It simply give probabilies against the whole vocab so that we can select the one with highest probability
